cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new dataset for speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the dataset includes face tracks and subtitles, which are visual and textual data.
- cs.SD (Sound) is another possible category as the dataset includes audio-visual speech data.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a relevant category as the dataset includes both visual and audio data.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the use of machine learning techniques for speech recognition on the dataset.
